   DEBUG: 2026-04-04 18:45:29,965:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Figure 2: Overall accuracy comparison across all five methods.
   DEBUG: 2026-04-04 18:45:30,012:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: TG-MAD achieves the highest accuracy (53.7%), a 3.3 percentage point improvement over the single-agent
   DEBUG: 2026-04-04 18:45:30,040:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: baseline. Notably, TG-MAD exhibits a dramatically higher correction rate (21.0%) compared to standard MAD
   DEBUG: 2026-04-04 18:45:30,054:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: (5.3%), indicating that optimized prompts encourage agents to change incorrect answers more actively. However,
   DEBUG: 2026-04-04 18:45:30,058:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: this comes with a trade-off: the subversion rate also increases to 18.3%, meaning agents sometimes change correct
   DEBUG: 2026-04-04 18:45:30,059:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: answers to incorrect ones during debate.
   DEBUG: 2026-04-04 18:45:30,060:      pdf_renderer.py:  235: /export/home3/dazhou/debate-or-vote/report/../out/tg_mad_hh_rlhf_qwen25_7b_peragent_r2_bs1_ep3_nh100_20260325_try2/subversion_correction_bar.png, 1500, 750
   DEBUG: 2026-04-04 18:45:30,082:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-04 18:45:30,084:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Figure 3: Correction, subversion, maintained-correct, and maintained-wrong rates across debate methods.
   DEBUG: 2026-04-04 18:45:30,084:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 5.2 Round-by-Round Dynamics
